Welcome to Abella 2.0.5. 
Abella < Kind nm type.


Abella < Kind pr type.


Abella < Type taup pr -> pr.


Abella < Type inp nm -> (nm -> pr) -> pr.


Abella < Type oup nm -> nm -> pr -> pr.


Abella < Type plus, par pr -> pr -> pr.


Abella < Type null pr.


Abella < Type nu (nm -> pr) -> pr.


Abella < Type match, mismatch nm -> nm -> pr -> pr.


Abella < Kind lb type.


Abella < Type tau lb.


Abella < Type up, dn nm -> nm -> lb.


Abella < Define name : A -> prop by 
nabla x, name x.


Abella < Define fresh : A -> B -> prop by 
nabla x, fresh x E.


Abella < Theorem quasi-em : 
nabla y, forall x, x = y \/ (x = y -> false).



============================
 nabla y, forall x, x = y \/ (x = y -> false)

quasi-em < skip.
Proof completed.

Abella < Define one : pr -> lb -> pr -> prop,	
oneb : pr -> (nm -> lb) -> (nm -> pr) -> prop by 
one (taup P) tau P;
one (inp X P) (dn X Y) (P Y);
one (oup X Y P) (up X Y) P;
one (plus P Q) L R := one P L R;
one (plus P Q) L R := one Q L R;
one (par P Q) L (par R Q) := one P L R;
one (par P Q) L (par P R) := one Q L R;
one (nu P) L (nu Q) := nabla x, one (P x) L (Q x);
one (match X X P) L Q := one P L Q;
one (mismatch X Y P) L Q := (name X \/ name Y) /\ (X = Y -> false) /\ one P L Q;
one (par P Q) tau (par PP QQ) := (exists X Y, one P (dn X Y) PP /\ one Q (up X Y) QQ) \/
  (exists X Y, one P (up X Y) PP /\ one Q (dn X Y) QQ);
one (par P Q) tau (nu (y\par (PP y) (QQ y))) := (exists X, oneb Q (up X) QQ /\ (nabla y, one P (dn X y) (PP y))) \/
  (exists X, oneb P (up X) PP /\ (nabla y, one Q (dn X y) (QQ y)));
oneb (nu P) (up X) R := nabla y, one (P y) (up X y) (R y);
oneb (plus P Q) L R := oneb P L R;
oneb (plus P Q) L R := oneb Q L R;
oneb (par P Q) L (x\par (R x) Q) := oneb P L R;
oneb (par P Q) L (x\par P (R x)) := oneb Q L R;
oneb (match X X P) L Q := oneb P L Q;
oneb (mismatch X Y P) L Q := (name X \/ name Y) /\ (X = Y -> false) /\ oneb P L Q;
oneb (nu P) L (y\nu (x\R x y)) := nabla x, oneb (P x) L (R x).


Abella < CoDefine qbisim : pr -> pr -> prop by 
qbisim P Q := (forall L P1, one P L P1 -> (exists Q1, one Q L Q1 /\ qbisim P1 Q1)) /\
  (forall X P1, oneb P (up X) P1 ->
       (exists Q1, oneb Q (up X) Q1 /\ (nabla z, qbisim (P1 z) (Q1 z)))) /\
  (forall L Q1, one Q L Q1 -> (exists P1, one P L P1 /\ qbisim P1 Q1)) /\
  (forall X Q1, oneb Q (up X) Q1 ->
       (exists P1, oneb P (up X) P1 /\ (nabla z, qbisim (P1 z) (Q1 z)))).

Abella < Theorem qbisim-sym : 
forall P Q, qbisim P Q -> qbisim Q P.



============================
 forall P Q, qbisim P Q -> qbisim Q P

qbisim-sym < coinduction.


CH : forall P Q, qbisim P Q -> qbisim Q P +
============================
 forall P Q, qbisim P Q -> qbisim Q P #

qbisim-sym < intros.

============================
 qbisim Q P #

qbisim-sym < case H1.

Abella < Theorem qbisim_cong_plus :

Abella < Define inv : (pr -> pr -> prop) -> pr -> pr -> prop by 
inv Rel P Q := Rel P Q;
inv Rel (par P1 P2) (par Q1 Q2) := inv Rel P1 Q1 /\ inv Rel P2 Q2;
inv Rel (nu P) (nu Q) := nabla x, inv Rel (P x) (Q x).


Abella < Define qbisiminv : pr -> pr -> prop by 
qbisiminv P Q := (forall L P1, one P L P1 -> (exists Q1, one Q L Q1 /\ inv qbisim P1 Q1)) /\
  (forall X P1, oneb P (up X) P1 ->
       (exists Q1, oneb Q (up X) Q1 /\ (nabla y, inv qbisim (P1 y) (Q1 y)))) /\
  (forall L Q1, one Q L Q1 -> (exists P1, one P L P1 /\ inv qbisim P1 Q1)) /\
  (forall X Q1, oneb Q (up X) Q1 ->
       (exists P1, oneb P (up X) P1 /\ (nabla y, inv qbisim (P1 y) (Q1 y)))).


Abella < Theorem inv_qbisiminv : 
forall P Q, inv qbisim P Q -> qbisiminv P Q.

 forall P Q, inv qbisim P Q -> qbisiminv P Q

Abella < Theorem qbisim_cong_par : 
forall P Q R S, qbisim P Q -> qbisim R S -> qbisim (par P R) (par Q S).



============================
 forall P Q R S, qbisim P Q -> qbisim R S -> qbisim (par P R) (par Q S)

qbisim_cong_par < intros.


Variables: P Q R S
H1 : qbisim P Q
H2 : qbisim R S
============================
 qbisim (par P R) (par Q S)

qbisim_cong_par < backchain inv_qbisim.
Proof completed.

Abella < Kind o' type.


Abella < Type tt, ff o'.


Abella < Type conj, disj o' -> o' -> o'.


Abella < Type boxMat, diaMat, boxDif, diaDif nm -> nm -> o' -> o'.


Abella < Type boxAct, diaAct lb -> o' -> o'.


Abella < Type boxOut, diaOut nm -> (nm -> o') -> o'.


Abella < Define sat : pr -> o' -> prop by 
sat P ff := false;
sat P tt;
sat P (conj A B) := sat P A /\ sat P B;
sat P (disj A B) := sat P A \/ sat P B;
sat P (boxMat X Y A) := X = Y -> sat P A;
sat P (diaMat X Y A) := X = Y /\ sat P A;
sat P (boxDif X Y A) := name X \/ name Y -> (X = Y -> false) -> sat P A;
sat P (diaDif X Y A) := (name X \/ name Y) /\ (X = Y -> false) /\ sat P A;
sat P (boxAct X A) := forall P1, one P X P1 -> sat P1 A;
sat P (diaAct X A) := exists P1, one P X P1 /\ sat P1 A;
sat P (boxOut X A) := forall Q, oneb P (up X) Q -> (nabla w, sat (Q w) (A w));
sat P (diaOut X A) := exists Q, oneb P (up X) Q /\ (nabla w, sat (Q w) (A w)).


Abella < Theorem dist_form0 : 
forall P Q, ((forall F, sat P F -> sat Q F) -> false) \/
  ((forall F, sat Q F -> sat P F) -> false) ->
  (forall F, (sat P F -> sat Q F) /\ (sat Q F -> sat P F)) -> false.

   ((forall F, sat Q F -> sat P F) -> false) ->
   (forall F, (sat P F -> sat Q F) /\ (sat Q F -> sat P F)) -> false

Abella < Theorem qbisim_sat_R :

 forall P Q F, qbisim P Q -> sat Q F -> sat P F

Abella < Theorem sateq_inp_forall : 
forall P Q X, (forall F, (sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F) /\
                   (sat (inp X Q) F -> sat (inp X P) F)) ->
  (forall F Y, (sat (P Y) F -> sat (Q Y) F) /\ (sat (Q Y) F -> sat (P Y) F)).



============================
 forall P Q X, (forall F, (sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F) /\
                    (sat (inp X Q) F -> sat (inp X P) F)) ->
   (forall F Y, (sat (P Y) F -> sat (Q Y) F) /\ (sat (Q Y) F -> sat (P Y) F))

sateq_inp_forall < intros.


Variables: P Q X F Y
H1 : forall F, (sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F) /\
       (sat (inp X Q) F -> sat (inp X P) F)
============================
 (sat (P Y) F -> sat (Q Y) F) /\ (sat (Q Y) F -> sat (P Y) F)

sateq_inp_forall < apply H1 with F = diaAct (dn X Y) F.


Variables: P Q X F Y
H1 : forall F, (sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F) /\
       (sat (inp X Q) F -> sat (inp X P) F)
H2 : sat (inp X P) (diaAct (dn X Y) F) -> sat (inp X Q) (diaAct (dn X Y) F)
H3 : sat (inp X Q) (diaAct (dn X Y) F) -> sat (inp X P) (diaAct (dn X Y) F)
============================
 (sat (P Y) F -> sat (Q Y) F) /\ (sat (Q Y) F -> sat (P Y) F)

sateq_inp_forall < split.

Abella < Theorem satimp_forall_inp : 
forall P Q X, (forall F Y, sat (P Y) F -> sat (Q Y) F) ->
  (forall F, sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F).

   (forall F, sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F)

Abella < Theorem sateq_forall_inp : 
forall P Q X, (forall F Y, (sat (P Y) F -> sat (Q Y) F) /\
                   (sat (Q Y) F -> sat (P Y) F)) ->
  (forall F, (sat (inp X P) F -> sat (inp X Q) F) /\
       (sat (inp X Q) F -> sat (inp X P) F)).

                    (sat (Q Y) F -> sat (P Y) F)) ->

        (sat (inp X Q) F -> sat (inp X P) F))

Abella < Theorem sat_diff1 :

       sat (mismatch X Y P) F

Abella < Theorem sateq_one_exists_L : 
forall P Q A P1, (forall F, (sat P F -> sat Q F) /\ (sat Q F -> sat P F)) ->
  one P A P1 -> (exists Q1, one Q A Q1).



============================
 forall P Q A P1, (forall F, (sat P F -> sat Q F) /\ (sat Q F -> sat P F)) ->
   one P A P1 -> (exists Q1, one Q A Q1)

                           (sat Q F -> sat P F)) ->

Abella < Theorem sateq_one_exists_R : 
forall P Q A Q1, (forall F, (sat P F -> sat Q F) /\ (sat Q F -> sat P F)) ->
  one Q A Q1 -> (exists P1, one P A P1).



============================
 forall P Q A Q1, (forall F, (sat P F -> sat Q F) /\ (sat Q F -> sat P F)) ->
   one Q A Q1 -> (exists P1, one P A P1)

             (plus (match x z (taup null)) (mismatch x z (taup null)))))
       (up X) Q1
============================
 exists P1, oneb (mismatch y z (taup (taup null))) (up X) P1 /\
   (nabla z1, qbisim (P1 z1) (Q1 z1))

mismatch_constructive_example < case H4.
Proof completed.
